headline: Dollar General Beats Estimates by 36% as Dollar Tree Stumbles
summary: Dollar General (NYSE: DG) and Dollar Tree (NASDAQ: DLTR) both reported November quarter results this week with wildly different outcomes. Dollar General beat earnings by 36% on December 4th, driving a 20% two-day rally. Dollar Tree missed estimates by 7.6% on December 2nd despite stronger revenue growth. headline: Why Dollar General (DG) Is Up 20.9% After Q3 Beat, Guidance Hike And Dividend Update
summary: In the past week, Dollar General reported third-quarter 2025 results showing sales of US$10,649.45 million and net income of US$282.66 million, raised full-year guidance for earnings and net sales growth, and its board declared a quarterly dividend of US$0.59 per share payable in January 2026.
